## Paper Summary: Energy and Policy Considerations for Modern Deep Learning Research
Authors: Strubell, E., Ganesh, A., & McCallum, A.
Year: 2020

### 1. Problem
Modern AI models are very large and need a lot of data and computing power. 
Which leads to high energy use, high cost, unfair research access and accuracy over efficiency. 


### 2. Approach
Research tested popular AI models like BERT and GPT – 2 and measured the following: 
1.	 Energy used from computers 
2.	Total power of data center cooling.
3.	Converted energy use into carbon emissions 
4.	Total Cost 



### 3. Key Findings
Ai training is growing extremely fast, faster than technology advancements. One training model can
produce hundreds of pounds of C02 and cost thousands of dollars. A full research project can cost over
100K. In many cases, researchers spend huge amounts of money to compute for very small improvements in
accuracy. An improvement is, better hardware such as TPUs that can help reduce energy use. 


### 4. Relevance to Our Topic
This source is relevant because it highlights the energy cost and challenges of using AI systems which 
directly connects to AI-driven network optimization. 


